The paper focuses on privacy-preserving collaborative deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also addresses the issue of privacy leakage, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper proposes a solution to handle unreliable participants, which involves data management and quality control, and thus could be categorized under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
